    • Class workshop.internal.entities.Classifier extends Trackable implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      50L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          java.lang.String name

        • description

          java.lang.String description

        • isOfficial

          boolean isOfficial
          Official Classifiers are presented in the official list of services. Non-official are made up on the spot to present a kind of services out of the official price list. Default = false (as Java primitive fields initialized by default)

        • price

          java.math.BigDecimal price
          The current price for the particular kind of services. It will be stored into Order at the moment of the Order creation to fix it, because this current price can be changed further. May be = 0 (some work for free, for instance). Default = 0.00;

          java.util.Set<E> tasks

    • Class workshop.internal.entities.Task extends Trackable implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      50L

      • Serialized Fields

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          If not explicitly given, all the included Classifiers names will be concatenated into this 'name' property.

        • deadline

          java.time.ZonedDateTime deadline

        • appointedTo

          Employee appointedTo

        • classifiers

          java.util.Set<E> classifiers
          One Task can have a number of Classifiers Validation note: this field is validated by setters To remove a Classifier with the Price recalculation use Task.removeClassifier(Classifier...) method!

        • order

          Order order

        • price

          java.math.BigDecimal price
          The sum of the all included Classifiers prices. Will be set automatically as the sum of the all included Classifiers prices. Use Task.addClassifier() of Task.deleteClassifier() to correctly set Task.price. Of course can be corrected manually. Default = 0.00

    • Class workshop.internal.entities.Trackable extends WorkshopEntityAbstract implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      50L

      • Serialized Fields

        • identifier

          java.lang.Long identifier
          Every instance has to '@Override public long getIdentifier() { return super.getIdentifier(); }' method so that not to clash ResourceSupport.getIdentifier() with WorkshopEntity.getIdentifier()

        • created

          java.time.ZonedDateTime created

        • modified

          java.time.ZonedDateTime modified

        • finished

          java.time.ZonedDateTime finished
          For Order and Task classes it is MUST BE null at creation time. But later after being set it is MAY BE an indicator of a finished work to send an OrderFinishedEvent to User if all the Tasks in the particular Order have their property Trackable.finished set.

        • createdBy

          Employee createdBy
          Sets automatically in the DaoAbstract.persistEntity() if an Employee is presented in the SecurityContext. Also may be set manually.

        • modifiedBy

          Employee modifiedBy
